        question: "My bayfront property on Balboa Peninsula gets water in the garage during king tides even though my bulkhead looks intact. Where is the water coming from?",
        answer: "Bay water during king tide events can enter through multiple pathways even when the bulkhead cap appears intact. The most common sources are gaps at the base of the bulkhead where the sheet pile meets the footing, corroded tie-back anchor penetrations, or water traveling laterally under the bulkhead through saturated fill soil. Water that enters through soil migration can travel 10 to 20 feet horizontally before appearing in a garage floor drain or at the base of a foundation wall. A professional evaluation should include inspection of the bulkhead cap, any penetrations through the seawall, and a drainage assessment of the lot grade between the bulkhead and the structure."
